## 7. Value-Add Suggestions

### QUICK WIN (< 1 day each)

| # | Suggestion | Why It Matters |
|---|-----------|---------------|
| QW1 | **Approval via WhatsApp reply.** When the morning brief lists pending invoices, let the developer reply "Approve 1" or "Approve all" directly in WhatsApp. The agent parses the reply and calls `on-approval-granted`. | Cuts developer daily time from 15 min to 5 min. The #1 product promise is minimal developer time. |
| QW2 | **Lead source badge on every lead card.** Show "📱 Meta · Diaspora UK · Creative A" as a coloured badge on the lead profile, not buried in a data field. | Makes attribution visible without navigating to a report. Sales agents see which leads are worth more. |
| QW3 | **"Copy Payment Details" button for buyers.** On the Buyer Portal payment page, a single tap copies bank name + account number + reference code to clipboard. | Nigerian buyers pay via mobile banking. Copy-paste eliminates typos in reference codes (which cause reconciliation failures). |
| QW4 | **WhatsApp delivery receipts visible to sales agents.** Show ✓ (sent), ✓✓ (delivered), 🔵 (read) status next to each message in the lead profile. | Sales agents know whether to follow up or wait. Sent but undelivered = phone issue, not disinterest. |
| QW5 | **Org health score in Super Admin.** A single 0–100 score per org based on: active leads, payment collection rate, GUARDIAN flag resolution rate, agent error rate. | Platform operators see at a glance which clients need attention. |

### FUTURE PHASE

| # | Suggestion | Why It Matters |
|---|-----------|---------------|
| FP1 | **Buyer referral programme.** Each buyer gets a unique referral link. If their referral converts, the buyer gets a credit or discount on their next instalment. | Word-of-mouth is the most powerful sales channel in Nigerian real estate. The system already has attribution tracking — this extends it. |
| FP2 | **Contractor bidding system.** For purchase requests above a threshold (e.g., ₦2M), allow 3 pre-qualified contractors to submit competing quotes within DEVOS. GUARDIAN compares all three. | Eliminates single-source bias. Developers see market rates in real time. |
| FP3 | **Construction milestone notifications for buyers.** When a progress update shows a phase reaching 25%, 50%, 75%, 100% complete, automatically send the buyer a WhatsApp update with a photo. | Keeps buyers engaged and reduces "is my house being built?" support queries. Current system updates the portal but doesn't proactively notify. |
| FP4 | **Developer mobile app (native).** The current plan includes a PWA. A native app (React Native) would enable push notifications for approval requests and hot leads, which is more reliable than WhatsApp for time-sensitive actions. | PWA push notifications are unreliable on iOS. The developer persona needs instant notification reliability. |
| FP5 | **AI-powered BOQ parsing.** Use Claude to extract structured rates and quantities from uploaded BOQ PDFs. Review and confirm via UI before committing to DB. | Removes the manual data entry step from budget setup, which is the most tedious part of onboarding. |

