## 8. Revised Assumptions & Open Questions

These were assumed in the PRD or plan and must be confirmed with a specific answer before coding begins.

| # | Question | Why It Matters | Default if No Answer |
|---|---------|---------------|---------------------|
| A1 | **Is the DEVOS Agent Engine a Supabase Edge Function, a standalone Node.js service, or something else?** | Determines hosting, scaling, cost model, and concurrency handling. This is the single most important architectural decision remaining. | Supabase Edge Function (stateless, per-invocation). |
| A2 | **How are Supabase Auth roles assigned?** Custom claims in JWT? `org_members.role` column checked at app level? Supabase Auth metadata? | RLS policies depend on this. Every permission check flows from this decision. | `org_members.role` column, with `get_user_org_id()` and `get_user_role()` helper functions used in RLS. |
| A3 | **Is Ollama on VPS in scope for MVP?** The PRD lists it for "lightweight classification/summarisation" but gives no specific use case. | If yes, it adds a VPS dependency. If no, all AI calls go to Claude API (simpler but more expensive). | Out of scope for MVP. All AI via Claude API + OpenRouter fallback. |
| A4 | **What bank does Primerose use, and does it support webhooks for payment confirmation?** | If yes, semi-automated payment confirmation is possible. If no, manual finance confirmation is the only path. | Manual confirmation. No bank webhook for MVP. |
| A5 | **Has legal review of document templates (Reservation Letter, Sale Agreement, Notice of Default) been initiated?** | These templates must be approved by a solicitor before pdf-mcp can generate them. Lead time is typically 2–4 weeks. | Must be initiated no later than Sprint 2 to be ready by Sprint 3 delivery. |
| A6 | **What is the approved monthly budget for Claude API calls?** | Without a cost cap, a high-volume sales campaign could generate thousands of API calls per day. | Set an org-level monthly API cost ceiling with alerting at 80%. Recommended: ₦200,000/month for Primerose MVP. |
| A7 | **Who is the approver for purchase requests vs invoices?** Is it always the developer (org_admin), or can it be delegated? | Affects the approval workflow and notification routing. | Developer (org_admin) only for MVP. Delegation is a Phase 4 feature. |
| A8 | **Is the `[slug].devos.app` domain structure confirmed?** Or will Primerose use a custom domain (primerose.ng)? | Affects Vercel configuration, SSL, and DNS setup in Sprint 1. | `[slug].devos.app` for MVP. Custom domains in Phase 5 (Enterprise tier). |
| A9 | **Is WhatsApp Business API tier already approved?** New WhatsApp Business accounts start with very low message limits (250/day). | A 200-unit project with active marketing could exceed this in Week 1. Business tier upgrade takes time. | Initiate WhatsApp Business verification now. Target Tier 2 (10,000 messages/day) before launch. |
| A10 | **What is the data retention policy for WhatsApp conversations?** | Stored in DEVOS forever? Purged after 12 months? Legal implications for buyer disputes. | Retained for the duration of the project + 1 year. Legal review recommended. |

