## 9. The Enhanced Summary Brief

> **This section is the single source of truth for the build team.** Read this in 5 minutes and know exactly what you're building.

---

### What We're Building

DEVOS is an AI-powered operating system for off-plan real estate developers. It has three modules:

1. **PRESELL** — Runs paid ads, captures leads, qualifies them via WhatsApp AI conversation, converts to reservation, manages payment plans, provides a buyer portal.
2. **GUARDIAN** — Monitors every purchase request and contractor invoice against market rates, BOQ, contracts, and site progress. Flags anomalies. Generates Payment Tickets. Produces JV partner reports.
3. **COMMAND** — A single dashboard + daily WhatsApp brief. Developer spends <20 min/day.

It is multi-tenant SaaS from Sprint 1. First client: Primerose Smart City Cluster (200 units, Rivers State).

### The Architecture in One Paragraph

React frontend on Vercel with wildcard subdomain routing (`[slug].devos.app`). Supabase backend: PostgreSQL with `organisation_id` on every table + RLS + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions. Supabase Edge Functions handle all deterministic events (lead created, invoice submitted, payment confirmed, scheduled reminders). When reasoning is needed, Edge Functions call the **DEVOS Agent Engine** — a stateless Claude API invocation scoped to one `organisation_id`, with MCP tools for WhatsApp, Meta Ads, email, and PDF generation. Per-org API credentials stored in Supabase Vault and injected at call time. OpenClaw (Law's personal AI) has read-only access to DEVOS data — it is not part of the product.

### The Four Agents

| Agent | Trigger | Core Behaviour | Tool Access |
|-------|---------|---------------|-------------|
| PRESELL | New lead, inbound WhatsApp | Multi-turn qualification, scoring, escalation | whatsapp-mcp, supabase-mcp |
| GUARDIAN | Purchase request, invoice submitted, weekly JV trigger | Analysis against BOQ/contract/market rates, flag generation, report writing | supabase-mcp, email-mcp, pdf-mcp |
| ADENGINE | Campaign setup, 48h optimisation cycle, ad fatigue detection | Performance analysis, budget reallocation, copy generation | meta-ads-mcp, tiktok-ads-mcp, veo3-mcp |
| MASTER | Daily 7am trigger | Cross-module synthesis, morning brief composition | whatsapp-mcp, supabase-mcp |

### Build Phases

| Phase | Weeks | Delivers |
|-------|-------|---------|
| **1 — Foundation** | 1–3 | Multi-tenant schema, landing page, lead capture, WhatsApp qualification, reservation flow, Buyer Portal MVP, Command Dashboard MVP, morning brief |
| **2 — GUARDIAN Core** | 4–6 | Budget setup, purchase request workflow, Contractor Portal, invoice verification, approval → Payment Ticket → finance chain, GUARDIAN dashboard, JV weekly report |
| **3 — Intelligence** | 7–10 | AdEngine (campaigns, Meta Ads integration, creative approval, performance dashboard, 48h optimisation, attribution tracking), predictive overrun engine, full Command Dashboard |
| **4 — Polish** | 11–14 | Sale Agreement generation, e-signature, Notice of Default, contractor scoring, error handling hardening, security audit, UAT, load testing |
| **5 — SaaS** | Months 4–6 | Onboarding wizard, subscription billing (Paystack + Stripe), white-label, Super Admin panel, marketing site, first 3 external clients |

### Critical Edge Cases That Must Be Handled

| # | Edge Case | Where | How |
|---|----------|-------|-----|
| 1 | Duplicate lead submission (same phone/email within 24h) | `on-lead-created` | Upsert — update existing lead, do not create duplicate, do not trigger new WhatsApp thread |
| 2 | WhatsApp webhook delivers same message twice | `on-whatsapp-inbound` | Check `message_id` against `whatsapp_threads`. Reject duplicate. |
| 3 | Claude API timeout during WhatsApp conversation | Agent Engine | 30s timeout → OpenRouter fallback → if both fail, queue message for retry in 5 min, send buyer "Thanks, we'll get back to you shortly" template |
| 4 | Two buyers attempt to reserve the same unit simultaneously | Reservation flow | Database-level: `SELECT FOR UPDATE` on the `units` row. First confirmed deposit wins. Second buyer is offered alternatives. |
| 5 | Contractor submits invoice for a phase marked <50% complete by site manager | `on-invoice-submitted` | GUARDIAN flags as CRITICAL. Invoice blocked. Site manager asked to verify. |
| 6 | Payment reference code typo (buyer sends wrong code) | Finance view | Finance can search by amount + date range + contractor name when reference doesn't match. System suggests best match. |
| 7 | Org slug collision (two orgs want "primerose") | Org creation | Slug uniqueness enforced at DB level (unique constraint). UI shows "this name is taken" instantly. |
| 8 | WhatsApp API rate limit exceeded | whatsapp-mcp | Queue excess messages. Process when rate limit resets. Alert super admin if queue exceeds 100 messages. |
| 9 | Lead goes 30+ turns without progressing past QUALIFYING | PRESELL Agent | Auto-escalate to human. Mark lead as NEEDS_INTERVENTION. |
| 10 | Exchange rate used in diaspora display is stale | Landing page / WhatsApp | Display "approximate rate as of [date]" disclaimer. Rate updated daily from a reliable API (e.g., exchangerate-api.com). |

### What "Done" Looks Like (Phase 1)

- [ ] A lead submits a form on `primerose.devos.app/buy` and receives a WhatsApp message within 60 seconds.
- [ ] The AI conducts a multi-turn qualification conversation, updates the lead score after each turn.
- [ ] When lead score hits 70+, the sales agent gets a notification with the full conversation thread.
- [ ] A buyer can reserve a unit, receive payment instructions with a unique reference, upload a receipt.
- [ ] Finance confirms the receipt. The unit status changes to "Reserved." The Buyer Portal activates. A Reservation Letter PDF is auto-generated and sent.
- [ ] The Command Dashboard shows live unit counts, revenue, and lead pipeline.
- [ ] The developer receives a morning brief at 7am via WhatsApp summarising overnight activity.
- [ ] All data is isolated by `organisation_id`. A second org's data is invisible.

### What "Done" Looks Like (Phase 2)

- [ ] A site manager submits a purchase request. GUARDIAN analyses it within 5 minutes and flags price/quantity anomalies.
- [ ] A contractor submits an invoice with evidence photos. GUARDIAN runs 6 checks and produces a flag report.
- [ ] Developer approves → Payment Ticket generated → Finance notified by email.
- [ ] Budget dashboard shows real-time spend vs plan with health indicators.
- [ ] JV report auto-delivered every Monday at 7am.
- [ ] Finance View shows all Payment Tickets pending and completed.

### What "Done" Looks Like (Phase 3)

- [ ] Developer creates a campaign in DEVOS. AdEngine generates copy variants. Developer approves. Ads go live on Meta.
- [ ] Every lead is attributed to the specific ad creative that generated it.
- [ ] AdEngine autonomously pauses underperformers and scales top performers every 48 hours.
- [ ] GUARDIAN predicts budget overruns 6–8 weeks in advance and alerts the developer.
- [ ] Revenue attribution report shows exact ROAS per ad, per audience, per platform.

