### Test Coverage Map

#### PRESELL Module

| Feature | Unit Test | Integration Test | Top 3 Edge Cases |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Lead scoring algorithm | Test each signal (+15 Lagos, +20 diaspora, -20 below min price, etc.) with known inputs → assert exact score | Lead form → Supabase → score calculated → correct score stored | 1. All positive signals = max 100 (not >100). 2. All negative signals = min 0 (not negative). 3. Score recalculated correctly after WhatsApp engagement signals added. |
| WhatsApp qualification flow | Test each state transition (INTAKE→QUALIFYING, QUALIFYING→HOT, etc.) with mock agent responses | Lead created → WhatsApp sent → reply received → agent responds → score updated → state changed | 1. Out-of-order messages (reply to Q1 arrives after Q2 sent). 2. Buyer sends media (photo/voice note) instead of text. 3. Conversation restarts after 48h silence (COLD re-entry). |
| Reservation workflow | Test unit status transitions (Available→Reserved, Reserved→Sold) with constraint enforcement | Buyer selects unit → payment instructions sent → receipt uploaded → finance confirms → Buyer Portal active → PDF generated | 1. Two simultaneous reservations on same unit. 2. Receipt uploaded but finance rejects (unit returns to Available). 3. Buyer reserves then goes silent for 14 days (reservation expiry policy needed). |
| Payment reminders | Test reminder trigger logic: 7d before, 3d before, due date, overdue escalation | Scheduled function fires → correct buyers identified → WhatsApp template sent → delivery confirmed | 1. Payment made between reminder schedule and send time (don't remind for paid instalments). 2. Buyer has no WhatsApp (fallback to email). 3. Multiple instalments overdue simultaneously (send one consolidated notice, not five). |

#### GUARDIAN Module

| Feature | Unit Test | Integration Test | Top 3 Edge Cases |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Purchase request analysis | Test price check (>5% flag), quantity check (>15% flag), budget check (>85% consumed flag), duplicate check (same item + supplier in 14d) | Site manager submits → Edge Function fires → GUARDIAN agent analyses → flags appear in developer dashboard | 1. Price exactly at 5% threshold (should it flag or not? Define: >5% flags). 2. Budget at 84.9% with new request pushing to 86% (flag, not block). 3. Two purchase requests for same material, different suppliers, same day (not a duplicate — different suppliers). |
| Invoice verification | Test each of 6 checks in isolation: rate vs contract, progress vs site manager report, quantity vs BOQ, cumulative BOQ, photo analysis, duplicate detection | Contractor submits invoice with photos → Edge Function → GUARDIAN analysis → flags generated → site manager verification → developer approval → Payment Ticket | 1. Contractor submits invoice for work not yet in any progress_update (no data to compare against). 2. Cumulative invoiced amount exactly equals BOQ allowance (flag as INFO, not block). 3. Two invoices from same contractor, same amount, different work items (not a duplicate — verify by description). |
| Approval → Payment Ticket | Test ticket PDF generation with correct fields, test finance email delivery | Developer approves → ticket created → PDF generated → email sent → finance marks PAID → budget updated | 1. Developer approves then immediately retracts (cancel Payment Ticket before finance processes). 2. Finance marks PAID but enters wrong amount (recording should match ticket amount, with option to note discrepancy). 3. Network failure during PDF generation (retry, don't leave approval in limbo). |

#### AdEngine Module

| Feature | Unit Test | Integration Test | Top 3 Edge Cases |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Campaign creation + Meta Ads publish | Test UTM link generation, test budget split calculation | Campaign created → creatives generated → developer approves → meta-ads-mcp publishes → ad_performance sync returns data | 1. Developer approves 0 of 3 generated creatives (campaign stays in DRAFT, nothing published). 2. Meta API rejects creative (wrong aspect ratio, policy violation) — surface error to developer with Meta's reason. 3. Campaign created with ₦0 budget (block at validation). |
| 48h optimisation cycle | Test ad fatigue detection logic (CTR decline >30% over 7d), test budget reallocation rules | Scheduled trigger → agent analyses → pauses underperformers → scales top performer budget by ≤40% → logs decisions | 1. All ad sets underperforming (don't pause everything — keep the least-bad one running and alert developer). 2. Budget reallocation would exceed daily spend cap (cap at approved amount). 3. Meta API rate limited during optimisation (queue actions, retry next cycle). |
| Lead attribution | Test attribution chain: ad_creative → lead → reservation → payments_in | Click tracking URL → lead form → lead created with source tag → reservation → attribution report shows revenue per creative | 1. Lead submits form organically (no UTM — attributed to "Direct/Organic"). 2. Lead clicks Ad A, then submits via Ad B link days later (last-click attribution — document this choice). 3. Lead converts but the original ad has been paused/deleted (attribution preserved, ad archived not deleted). |

#### Cross-Module

| Feature | Unit Test | Integration Test | Top 3 Edge Cases |
|---------|-----------|-----------------|-------------------|
| Morning brief | Test data compilation — correct lead count, payment total, flag count for a given org | 7am trigger → data snapshot → MASTER agent composes → WhatsApp sent to developer | 1. Zero overnight activity (brief should say "All clear — nothing requires your attention" not send an empty template). 2. Agent Engine fails during brief composition (send a fallback: "Morning brief generation failed. Check your dashboard."). 3. Multiple organisations (each developer gets only their org's brief, at their org's timezone). |
| Multi-tenancy isolation | Test that RLS blocks cross-org read/write on every table | Create 2 orgs → insert data in org A → query as org B user → assert 0 rows returned; attempt write to org A row as org B user → assert error | 1. Service role key used without org_id parameter (must be blocked or logged as critical). 2. User moved from org A to org B (old org data immediately invisible). 3. Super admin impersonation mode (read-only flag must be enforced at DB level, not just UI). |

